# Case 4 North Star

Treat the end product as a sentiment-driven prediction system for post-earnings stock direction, while allowing iterative prototype quality during development.

- Always prioritize features that support:
  - baseline vs sentiment-enhanced model comparison
  - company-level sentiment + cross-company spillover features
  - five-trading-day post-earnings direction prediction
- Keep strict leakage controls: only use information available in the 7-day window ending at earnings date `T`.
- Use time-aware validation and avoid random splits that leak future information.
- Ensure outputs are explainable: show source links, feature rationale, spillover path, and confidence.
- Prefer practical pipeline steps over perfect modeling early; optimize quality after end-to-end flow works.
- When proposing changes, tie them back to one of these deliverables:
  - data pipeline
  - sentiment methodology
  - feature design
  - validation approach
  - dashboard visual evidence
  - findings and improvement roadmap

